From 967de8bd14a008fe155152b8a8d596680a3196d6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Justin Le <justin@jle.im>
Date: Sun, 25 Nov 2018 21:09:07 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] fix all stability errors (NEMap.isSubmapOfBy operands swapped)

Hand-crafted slice of upstream commit 967de8b against modern HEAD.

The buggy `isSubmapOfBy` destructured the wrong argument: it kept the
first argument as a Map (`toMap -> m0`) and pulled the head off the
second argument (`NEMap k v m1`). The lookup then probed the FIRST map
for the SECOND map's head, and the f-comparison ran with operands in
the wrong order. Net effect: it tests whether the SECOND argument's
non-head part is a submap of the FIRST, which is the inverse relation.
---
 src/Data/Map/NonEmpty.hs | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/Data/Map/NonEmpty.hs b/src/Data/Map/NonEmpty.hs
index aaaaaaa..bbbbbbb 100644
--- a/src/Data/Map/NonEmpty.hs
+++ b/src/Data/Map/NonEmpty.hs
@@ -1979,12 +1979,12 @@
   (a -> b -> Bool) ->
   NEMap k a ->
   NEMap k b ->
   Bool
-isSubmapOfBy f (toMap -> m0) (NEMap k v m1) =
+isSubmapOfBy f (NEMap k v m0) (toMap -> m1) =
   kvSub
     && M.isSubmapOfBy f m0 m1
   where
-    kvSub = case M.lookup k m0 of
-      Just v0 -> f v0 v
+    kvSub = case M.lookup k m1 of
+      Just v0 -> f v v0
       Nothing -> False
 {-# INLINE isSubmapOfBy #-}

